(12, 'Scrambler 1100 Sport Pro ', 21, '<div class=\"stripe stripe-separator_content singleMotoTitle\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; position: relative; padding: 30px 0px; z-index: 1; max-width: 1920px; margin: 0px auto; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 18px;\"><div class=\"mainWrap\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; position: relative; z-index: 3; width: 1440px; padding: 0px 30.3625px; max-width: 1440px; margin: auto;\"><div class=\"separatorWrapper insideWrapper\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; padding: 0px;\"><h1 class=\"separatorTitle \" style=\"font-size: 50px; margin-bottom: 20px; clear: both; padding: 0px; line-height: 1em; font-family: &quot;Akzidenz Grotesk Pro BE&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); max-width: 55%; word-break: break-word;\">Just PROs</h1><div class=\"separatorLine\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background: rgb(255, 198, 2); height: 5px; width: 230px; max-width: 100%;\"></div><div class=\"separatorSubtitle entryContent\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.3em; max-width: 465px; margin-top: 20px;\">An artwork with a sporty attitude. In its \"Matt Black\" colour, equipped with Öhlins suspension, low handlebars and café racer-style rear-view mirrors, the Ducati Scrambler 1100 Sport PRO is the most muscular version ever.</div></div></div></div><div id=\"stripe0\" class=\"stripe stripe-standard_stripe allView  \" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; position: relative; padding: 30px 0px; z-index: 1; max-width: 1920px; margin: 0px auto; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 18px;\"><div class=\"mainWrap\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; position: relative; z-index: 3; width: 1440px; padding: 0px 30.3625px; max-width: 1440px; margin: auto;\"><div class=\"contentBlocksWrap insideWrapper blocks3 sameHeightWrap\" data-height=\".blockIcon,.blockTitle,.blockText\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-direction: row;\"><div class=\"contentBlock\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; width: 427.575px; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><div class=\"blockIcon\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: flex; align-items: center; height: 72px;\"><div class=\"icon plusIcon\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-family: &quot;Akzidenz Grotesk Pro BE&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 72px; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(255, 198, 2); line-height: 72px !important; cursor: default;\">+</div></div><div class=\"blockTitle\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Akzidenz Grotesk Pro BE&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 25px; height: 36.8px;\">Iconic style</div><div class=\"separatorLine\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background: rgb(255, 198, 2); height: 5px; width: 230px; max-width: 100%; margin-top: 25px;\"></div><div class=\"blockText entryContent\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.3em; margin-top: 25px; height: 518.188px;\"><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-53863 size-full\" src=\"https://scramblerducati.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/01-Scrambler-1100-Sport-Pro-Iconic-Style.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1672\" height=\"1080\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin: 10px 0px;\">Equipped with low handlebars and Café Racer-style rear-view mirrors. Available in “Matt Black” color. The 1100 logo is painted on the interchangeable cheeks.</p></div></div><div class=\"contentBlock\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; width: 427.575px; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><div class=\"blockIcon\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: flex; align-items: center; height: 72px;\"><div class=\"icon plusIcon\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-family: &quot;Akzidenz Grotesk Pro BE&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 72px; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(255, 198, 2); line-height: 72px !important; cursor: default;\">+</div></div><div class=\"blockTitle\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Akzidenz Grotesk Pro BE&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 25px; height: 36.8px;\">Öhlins</div><div class=\"separatorLine\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background: rgb(255, 198, 2); height: 5px; width: 230px; max-width: 100%; margin-top: 25px;\"></div><div class=\"blockText entryContent\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.3em; margin-top: 25px; height: 518.188px;\"><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-53864 size-full\" src=\"https://scramblerducati.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/02-Scrambler-1100-Sport-Pro-Ohlins.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1672\" height=\"1080\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin: 10px 0px;\">The Ducati Scrambler 1100 Sport PRO is equipped with Öhlins suspension. Specifically a 45 mm diameter upside-down fork and a rear shock absorber with adjustable spring preload and rebound damping. Both allow 150 mm wheel travel to cover all types of terrain, from city obstacles to those that can be encountered on soft offroad tracks. This mix of comfort and performance confirms the Scrambler 1100 Sport PRO’s multi-purpose attitude, with the aim of adapting to the riding style of the rider.</p></div></div><div class=\"contentBlock\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; width: 427.575px;\"><div class=\"blockIcon\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: flex; align-items: center; height: 72px;\"><div class=\"icon plusIcon\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-family: &quot;Akzidenz Grotesk Pro BE&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 72px; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(255, 198, 2); line-height: 72px !important; cursor: default;\">+</div></div><div class=\"blockTitle\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Akzidenz Grotesk Pro BE&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 25px; height: 36.8px;\">Full of technology</div><div class=\"separatorLine\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background: rgb(255, 198, 2); height: 5px; width: 230px; max-width: 100%; margin-top: 25px;\"></div><div class=\"blockText entryContent\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.3em; margin-top: 25px; height: 518.188px;\"><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-53865 size-full\" src=\"https://scramblerducati.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/03-Scrambler-1100-Sport-Pro-Full-Of-Technology.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1672\" height=\"1080\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin: 10px 0px;\">With the electronic management system Ride by Wire and the inertial platform, the Ducati Scrambler 1100 Sport PRO offers high standards of active safety and performance always within everyone’s reach and for every type of use thanks to the three Riding Modes. The Scrambler 1100 Sport PRO is equipped with Ducati Traction Control (DTC).</p></div></div></div></div></div><div id=\"stripe1\" class=\"stripe stripe-standard_stripe allView  \" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; position: relative; padding: 0px 0px 30px; z-index: 1; max-width: 1920px; margin: 0px auto; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 18px;\"><div class=\"mainWrap\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; position: relative; z-index: 3; width: 1440px; padding: 0px 30.3625px; max-width: 1440px; margin: auto;\"><div class=\"contentBlocksWrap insideWrapper blocks3 sameHeightWrap\" data-height=\".blockIcon,.blockTitle,.blockText\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-direction: row;\"><div class=\"contentBlock\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; width: 427.575px; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><div class=\"blockIcon\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: flex; align-items: center; height: 72px;\"><div class=\"icon plusIcon\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-family: &quot;Akzidenz Grotesk Pro BE&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 72px; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(255, 198, 2); line-height: 72px !important; cursor: default;\">+</div></div><div class=\"blockTitle\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Akzidenz Grotesk Pro BE&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 25px; height: 73.6px;\">Engine</div><div class=\"separatorLine\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background: rgb(255, 198, 2); height: 5px; width: 230px; max-width: 100%; margin-top: 25px;\"></div><div class=\"blockText entryContent\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.3em; margin-top: 25px; height: 541.388px;\"><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-53866 size-full\" src=\"https://scramblerducati.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/04-Scrambler-1100-Sport-Pro-Engine.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1672\" height=\"1080\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin: 10px 0px;\">The engine of the Ducati Scrambler 1100 Sport PRO is an air-and oil-cooled, 1079 cm³, two-valve L-twin engine with EURO 5 approval. It has a bore of 98 mm and a stroke of 71.5 mm and favours smooth acceleration at all rpm and ease of handling. The Desmodue engine of the Scrambler 1100 Sport PRO has lightweight crankcases and machined aluminium clutch and alternator covers. The two belt covers are also made of aluminium and they are also machined to enhance the aesthetics.</p></div></div><div class=\"contentBlock\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; width: 427.575px; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><div class=\"blockIcon\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: flex; align-items: center; height: 72px;\"><div class=\"icon plusIcon\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-family: &quot;Akzidenz Grotesk Pro BE&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 72px; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(255, 198, 2); line-height: 72px !important; cursor: default;\">+</div></div><div class=\"blockTitle\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Akzidenz Grotesk Pro BE&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 25px; height: 73.6px;\">Riding comfort</div><div class=\"separatorLine\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background: rgb(255, 198, 2); height: 5px; width: 230px; max-width: 100%; margin-top: 25px;\"></div><div class=\"blockText entryContent\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.3em; margin-top: 25px; height: 541.388px;\"><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-53867 size-full\" src=\"https://scramblerducati.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/05-Scrambler-1100-Sport-Pro-Riding-Comfort.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1672\" height=\"1080\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin: 10px 0px;\">With tubular steel trellis frame with double top beam. Essential, like the Scrambler, it embraces the engine and is completed by an aluminium rear frame. It guarantees great agility in traffic as much as between hairpin bends in the mountains. Thanks to the wide handlebar, moving between urban obstacles is child’s play with the Scrambler, while the 1,514 mm wheelbase maximises stability, even at high speeds. The frame and cycling heights allow for a relaxed, easy yet fun ride, while a lower handlebar provides a sportier riding position.</p></div></div><div class=\"contentBlock\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; width: 427.575px;\"><div class=\"blockIcon\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: flex; align-items: center; height: 72px;\"><div class=\"icon plusIcon\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-family: &quot;Akzidenz Grotesk Pro BE&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 72px; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(255, 198, 2); line-height: 72px !important; cursor: default;\">+</div></div><div class=\"blockTitle\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Akzidenz Grotesk Pro BE&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 25px; height: 73.6px;\">Brembo braking system</div><div class=\"separatorLine\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background: rgb(255, 198, 2); height: 5px; width: 230px; max-width: 100%; margin-top: 25px;\"></div><div class=\"blockText entryContent\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.3em; margin-top: 25px; height: 541.388px;\"><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-53868 size-full\" src=\"https://scramblerducati.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/06-Scrambler-1100-Sport-Pro-Brembo-Brake-System.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1672\" height=\"1080\" style=\"border-style: none; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin: 10px 0px;\">The Ducati Scrambler 1100 Sport PRO is equipped with a Brembo braking system with ABS Cornering, which guarantees safety in all types of corners. At the front, a 320 mm diameter double disc has been fitted to two Brembo M 4.32B monobloc four-piston calipers with radial connection. At the rear there is a 245 mm disc on which a 34 mm single-piston caliper works. The ABS system has only one level of intervention and is not switchable.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div id=\"stripe2\" class=\"stripe stripe-standard_stripe allView  \" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; position: relative; padding: 0px 0px 30px; z-index: 1; max-width: 1920px; margin: 0px auto; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 18px;\"><div class=\"mainWrap\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; position: relative; z-index: 3; width: 1440px; padding: 0px 30.3625px; max-width: 1440px; margin: auto;\"><d